# Security Policy for TeleBots
# Last updated: 2025-01-04

## Contact Information
- Email: roman.fedoniuk@gmail.com
- Website: https://telebots.site
- Phone: +380960908006

## Scope
This security policy applies to:
- telebots.site and all subdomains
- All services and applications hosted on our infrastructure
- All client projects and data

## Supported Versions
We provide security updates for the following versions:
- Current version: 2025.1.0
- Previous version: 2024.12.0 (until 2025-02-04)

## Reporting a Vulnerability
If you discover a security vulnerability, please report it to us:

1. **Email**: roman.fedoniuk@gmail.com
2. **Subject**: Security Vulnerability Report
3. **Include**:
   - Description of the vulnerability
   - Steps to reproduce
   - Potential impact
   - Suggested fix (if any)

## Response Timeline
- **Initial response**: 24 hours
- **Status update**: 7 days
- **Resolution**: 30 days (depending on complexity)

## What We're Looking For
- Cross-site scripting (XSS)
- Cross-site request forgery (CSRF)
- SQL injection
- Authentication bypass
- Authorization flaws
- Information disclosure
- Remote code execution
- Server-side request forgery (SSRF)
- Insecure direct object references
- Security misconfiguration

## What We're NOT Looking For
- Social engineering attacks
- Physical attacks
- Denial of service attacks
- Issues in third-party applications
- Issues that require physical access to the device
- Issues that require social engineering
- Issues that require access to internal systems

## Recognition
We will acknowledge security researchers who responsibly disclose vulnerabilities and may include them in our security acknowledgments page.

## Legal
This policy is for security researchers only. Any activities that violate applicable laws are not covered by this policy.

## Changes
This policy may be updated from time to time. The latest version will always be available at https://telebots.site/security-policy
